competitions.rules: Tis the season to be merry, so for this month, your speedruns will need to focus on snowballs! These objects can be thrown, bounced on, and bonked in endless combinations, so get creative with your setups to really wow the judges! Additionally, we’ve allowed the use of spikeballs for any grinches out there. Happy making!

competition_group.name: Speedrun Showcase
competition_group.rules:
The Speedrun Showcase is a monthly level creation competition designed to help you flex your creative muscles! Each month has a different theme required for the entries, and the winners get a special medal on the TeamSpeedrun website. The theme will be announced on the first of every month, and the final day for entries is 4 days before the end of the month.
In order to enter, simply make a level within the limits of the theme and submit it to the team with the Speedrun Showcase tag! For levels to be considered, they must meet the requirements for a TeamSpeedrun level set in the #rules discord channel.

competitions.rules: These magical mushrooms (or feathers, or leafs, or bells, you get the idea) have the power to give Mario a myriad of different abilities. Finding interesting and creative uses for the different abilities granted by these powerups will be the focus of this month's competition! Powerup swapping is allowed, but not required.

competitions.rules: This month’s competition is gonna be a tough one. The theme is autoscroll! From jumping through a vertical level, speedrunning through scrolling one-screen rooms, or changing things up with custom autoscroll, this useful tool is great for giving the player lots of time to react to incoming obstacles! But be careful: ensuring the player is not slowed down by the autoscroll is a must! If you have any questions, feel free to ask them in the #speedrun-showcase-chat!
